| Jenkins | Latest |
| Python | Optional |

---

# 🚀 Verify Installation

## Docker

```bash
docker --version
```

---

## AWS CLI

```bash
aws --version
```

---

## Git

```bash
git --version
```

---

# ☁️ AWS Configuration

Configure AWS CLI:

```bash
aws configure
```

Provide:

- AWS Access Key
- AWS Secret Key
- Region
- Output format

Example:

```text
Region: ap-south-1
Output: json
```

---

# 📥 Clone Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/n3meshram/docker-app.git

cd docker-app
```

---

# 🚀 Run Application Locally

## Build Docker Image

```bash
docker build -t flask-demo .
```

---

## Run Docker Container

```bash
docker run -d -p 5000:5000 --name flask-container flask-demo
```

---

# 🌐 Access Application

Open browser:

```text
http://localhost:5000
```

Expected Output:

```text
Jenkins Docker Pipeline Working!
```

---

# 🚀 Docker Compose Setup

## Start Multi-container Application

```bash
docker compose up -d
```

---

## Verify Running Containers

```bash
docker ps
```

---

## Stop Compose Application

```bash
docker compose down
```

---

# 🚀 Amazon ECR Setup

## Create ECR Repository

```bash
aws ecr create-repository \
  --repository-name flask-demo \
  --region ap-south-1
```

---

# 🔐 Authenticate Docker to ECR

```bash
aws ecr get-login-password --region ap-south-1 | \
docker login \
--username AWS \
--password-stdin <ACCOUNT_ID>.dkr.ecr.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com
```

Replace:

```text
<ACCOUNT_ID>
```

with your AWS account ID.

---

# 🚀 Tag Docker Image

```bash
docker tag flask-demo:latest \
<ACCOUNT_ID>.dkr.ecr.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/flask-demo:v1
```

---

# 🚀 Push Docker Image to ECR

```bash
docker push \
<ACCOUNT_ID>.dkr.ecr.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/flask-demo:v1
```

---

# 🚀 Pull Docker Image from ECR

```bash
docker pull \
<ACCOUNT_ID>.dkr.ecr.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/flask-demo:v1
```

---

# 🚀 Jenkins Pipeline

Current pipeline stages:

- Checkout Code
- Build Docker Image
- Authenticate to ECR
- Tag Docker Image
- Push Docker Image
- Cleanup Docker Resources

---

# 🧠 Image Versioning Strategy

Implemented image versioning using:

```text
BUILD_NUMBER
```

Example:

```text
flask-demo:1
flask-demo:2
flask-demo:3
```

Benefits:

- Deployment traceability
- Rollback support
- Immutable deployments

---

# 🛠️ Common Docker Commands

## List Images

```bash
docker images
```

---

## List Containers

```bash
docker ps -a
```

---

## View Container Logs

```bash
docker logs <container-name>
```

---

## Stop Container

```bash
docker stop <container-name>
```

---

## Remove Container

```bash
docker rm <container-name>
```

---

## Remove Image

```bash
docker rmi <image-name>
```

